{
  "stem": "19111.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I said, I must hold on, even if it's to be a witness to tell the story, the tragedy of our people.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 11 SECONDS] That lasted till somewheres in April of 1945.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And at one point, towards the end of April 1945, they told everybody from the camp to get out on a roll call.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they marched us to the train.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they put us on a train.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We found out later on that they were trying to get us either to the Alps and kill us because Auschwitz and all the other camps were already bombed out and taken over by the Russian Armies over there.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And a lot of other people, they just marched to the Alps.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The marches where-- most-- a lot of them died right just marching through the-- through the cold nights and days.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They put us on the train.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And on the train-- train took off-- now, the train was boxcars, but there were no roofs on it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So all the people were put in like sardines.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was very, very dense, with these striped uniforms that, that we were wearing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one day in the morning, we take a look.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We wound up right next to a German train, with-- where every third car had an anti-aircraft cannon, cannon on it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And sure enough, in a-- in a short while ensued a, a-- we were right in the midst of the war.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In other words, the Germans were trying to camouflage themselves with showing that there were prisoners in the next car.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's why there were cars without the roofs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the United States airplanes-- the fighter bombers came running and making sorties right on the entire length of the train.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they bombed out the locomotives.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
